<TITLE> Poland edge Albania 1-0 in friendly </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 WARSAW, May 28 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - An early goal by Maciej Zurawski gave Poland a 1-0 victory over Albania on Tuesday as they limbered up for next month's European championship. Zurawski struck in the third minute, capitalising on a long throw-in by Marcin Wasilewski to score Poland's 1,200th goal in international football. The hosts created several more goalscoring chances but failed to take advantage. Poland forward Euzebiusz Smolarek said: "We could have been better, but I see this as training." The Poles face Denmark in another home friendly on June 1 in Chorzow before heading off to the June 7-29 tournament, where they are in Group B with co-hosts Austria, Germany and Croati
